      "body" : "As another interesting sidenote, contrary to what it's written in the documentation, bn_get_word ignores the sign. So -255 returns 255 (the documentation says \"BN_get_word() returns the value a, and 0xffffffffL if a cannot be represented as an unsigned long.\" http://linux.die.net/man/3/bn_get_word , but clearly -255 can't be represented as an unsigned long)",
